{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB2045", "title": "Habitat Restoration and Enhancement Act.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["HabitatRestorationandEnhancementAct"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "The Habitat Restoration and Enhancement Act authorizes a project proponent to submit a habitat restoration or enhancement project to the Director of Fish and Wildlife for approval. Under the act, a habitat restoration or enhancement project is a project with the primary purpose of improving fish and wildlife habitat. The act requires the director to approve a habitat restoration or enhancement project if the director determines that specified conditions are met. Under the act, the director's approval of a habitat restoration or enhancement project is in lieu of any other permit, agreement, license, or other approval issued by the Department of Fish and Wildlife. The act makes moneys in the Habitat Restoration and Enhancement Account available to the department, upon appropriation by the Legislature, for the purposes of administering and implementing the act. Existing law repeals the act on January 1, 2027.\n\nThis bill would extend the operation of the act until January 1, 2032, and would require the department to submit a report on the implementation of the act to the Legislature no later than December 31, 2029."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab2045"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-17", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 20.", "date": "2026-02-18", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on W., P., & W.", "date": "2026-03-02", "organization_id":